To capitalize on Asia 's fastest-growing economy McDonald 's opened its first outlet in South Korea .
Moving into communist countries , on March 24 , 1988 it opened in Belgrade , Yugoslavia .
There to compete with the locally favored '' pljeskavica '' , a pork and onion sandwich , initial reaction was favorable .
Two years later came its largest outlet to date .
In Moscow thousands lined up for an opening day record of 30,000 meals being served at 27 cash registers .
Next , McDonald 's opened in China , where cooking is a culinary art .
McDonald 's worldwide restaurants are joint ventures with locals of the country in which they operate .
